Abstract = {{The material basis of a sustainable society will depend on chemical
   products and processes that are designed following principles that make
   them conducive to life. Important inherent properties of molecules need
   to be considered from the earliest stage-the design stage-to address
   whether compounds and processes are depleting versus renewable, toxic
   versus benign, and persistent versus readily degradable. Products,
   feedstocks, and manufacturing processes will need to integrate the
   principles of green chemistry and green engineering under an expanded
   definition of performance that includes sustainability considerations.
   This transformation will require the best of the traditions of science
   and innovation coupled with new emerging systems thinking and systems
   design that begins at the molecular level and results in a positive
   impact on the global scale.}},
